# Problem
Training is too slow. I'm trying different strategies to optimize training times and increase sample efficiency

# Solution
Experiment **batch_maddpg_trial** did a hyperparameter sweep searching for the best parameters that allow us to run batch MADDPG learning without sacrificing training performance. Two solutions were tried:
- lr-0.0008  num_optimizer_steps-2 grad_clip-3 (this one)
- lr-0.003 num_optimizer_steps-10 grad_clip-0

# Results
Run lr-0.0008  num_optimizer_steps-2 grad_clip-3 (this one) did not achieve good results.